at the amplitude of their light curves is correlated\nneither with rotation nor with mass. Once single stars and wide components of\nmultiple systems are separated from close components of multiple systems, the\nrotation period distributions exhibit a well defined dependence on mass that\nallows to make a meaningful comparison with similar distributions of either\nyounger or older associations/clusters. Such cleaned distributions allow to use\nthe stellar rotation period as age indicator, meaningfully for F and G type\nstars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 6 Jul 2017 08:34:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-11-01"}
